This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for face parsing, which involves segmenting an image of a face into different regions based on semantic labels. The paper also discusses the use of a continuous Conditional Random Field (C-CRF) network, which is a probabilistic graphical model commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) applications. Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which are a popular tool in multimedia (MM) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method using various metrics, which is a common theme in neural network (NE) research.
